post_text:
IMPORTANT BUS INFORMATION FOR MONDAY, SEPTEMBER 14!

On Monday, September 14, the driver for bus 111 will not be available to drive the PM route. There is not a sub available to cover, therefore, we are going to hold those students until another bus returns, this will be about a 45 minute delay.

If you are able to pick up your child in the afternoon this day, that would be great! Please call the building that your child attends and let them know in advance that you will be picking them up. If that is not an option they will be 45 minutes later than their normal drop off time.

We are very sorry for any inconvenience! Thank you for your understanding!

Shelly Mead,
Transportation Dept.
517-867-7898

post_text:
COMMENCEMENT:
The commencement parade is tomorrow at 10:00. From the back (west) parking lot near the football stadium. Seniors will be driven in vehicles through the HS driveway where they will walk across the stage, receive their diploma, photo opportunity, sign decision day banner, and pick up their school packet. The graduates vehicle will continue on to the east HS parking lot to turn tassels; the family vehicle will drive into town. At the completion of the tassel turning all graduates will be lead by the fire department into the village for the parade. If youd like to volunteer yet please contact Missy Keeler or Kristina Newsome. The weather forecast is favorable for Saturday with temperatures in the low 70s but if we need to postpone until 10:00 Sunday a decision will be made around 6:00AM Saturday and an Alert Solutions message will be broadcast to the district and on social media.
Tune into K105.3 on the radio or you can watch live here on our Facebook Page!

ATTN: Class of 2020 Graduates and family members: Commencement is Saturday, June 27, please plan to arrive at the following times for line up in the West parking lot (behind Elementary):
8:30 am Top 10
8:45 am A-D

Hope for no rain and a great day!!

post_text:
Dual Enrollment Students,

In order to successfully complete Fall registration, students must complete the following:

Complete the dual enrollment agreement form
Find a class you wish to take
Complete the application form for the particular school
Send Mrs. Huff all completed forms to pattie.huff@springportschools.net

All resources may be found in the Dual Enrollment section of our counseling website. Each College or University is different when it comes to their deadlines so please do not delay. All paperwork must be completed by June 15th in order to take an DE course in the Fall. If this process is not complete by June 15th, you will have to sign up for a high school class to complete your schedule.

post_text:
FOX 47 News have just created a resource to help recognize all of the graduating seniors within FOX 47's Mid-Michigan Viewing Area.

In this FREE resource students, parents, and others can upload a video shout-out to say thanks, farewell or any other message they wish to share. Pictures can also be uploaded as a tribute to the student's success as well. You can find all of your schools listed at this website: https://www.fox47news.com/grad

Also, attached is a simple step-by-step 1-sheet showing you and your students, parents and other community members exactly how to use this fun & unique resource!

We know this is an unprecedented time, and we want to say thank you for all that you are doing to support the education and success of our youth!

As of 4/13/2020 and continuing through 6/4/2020, Springport Public Schools will provide packaged meals for anyone age 18 and under.

Individuals will be able to pick up meals at the following (6) locations. Children do not need to be present.

Parents can pick up the meals for all children in their household. Meals may not be eaten on site; individuals are asked to pick up the meals to take home.

SCHOOL BUSES ON-SITE: 11:45 AM UNTIL 12:30 PM

-- GRACE FREEWILL BAPTIST CHURCH, 16680 E. Michigan Ave, Albion

-- CLARENCE TOWNSHIP HALL, 27052 R. Drive North, Albion

-- N. PARMA CHURCH, 11970 Devereaux Rd., Parma

-- POPE UNITED METHODIST CHURCH, 10025 N. Parma Rd, Springport

-- SPRING HARBOR MOBILE HOME PARK, Green St., Springport

-- SPRINGPORT HIGH SCHOOL, behind school by Cafe/Gym entrance

Families of high school students - checking in and making sure you are staying home and staying safe. Teachers are submitting 3rd Quarter grades so students need to reach out if there is something that still needs to be turned in. This is ONLY for assignments PRIOR to our shut down on March 13. Check PowerSchool to be sure. This is NOT in reference to the packets we sent home ON the 13th but if you would like to submit those to the teacher you may do so via email/photos. Email addresses are all firstname.lastname@springportschools.net

Feel free to reach out to teachers individually if you would like access to more content! We are here to help. Let us know what you need!

Should this closure be extended we want to know how to best support our families so we are gathering data on internet access etc. Please complete the survey below.

post_text: As a directive from the Governor, Springport Public Schools will be closed to students from this evening through April 5th. Essential staff only will report for deep cleaning. The main offices will be open from 8am-2pm on Monday, March 16th ONLY for parents to pick up work if students were absent today. Breakfast and Lunch Meet Up to Eat Up will be available for pick up outside the back door of the high school near the kitchen/locker rooms, at the Green Street Apartments, Onandaga Church or Small Blessings daycare in Eaton Rapids. Stay safe and keep reading!

shared_text:
AgroExpo
December 2, 2019 at 6:55 AM 路

The Michigan FFA Crop Management Challenge is a competition for FFA students that is designed to help students develop sound agronomic, marketing, and environmental decisions in a demonstration plot. In 2019, the students were judged on 35% yield of their corn plots, 35% economics, and 30% presentation/response to the questions.

The winners for 2019 are:

1st. Springport FFA
Students: Luke Betz, Cole Twiss, Ryan Henne, Eli Lighter
Coach: Megan Merrill
Field expert: DJ Hisler

2nd. Coleman FFA
Students: Jacob Rivard, Clayton Wishowski, Cole Johnston
Coach: Eric Fischer
Field experts: Phil Tuggle, Frank Zwemmer, Dave Wishowski, Kyle Elder

3rd. Ovid-Elsie FFA
Students: Joseph Duckert, Ben Maynard, Emma Fox, Tori Maynard, Caleb Love
Coach: Tracey Hoffman
Field experts: Burt Henry, Tim Duckert, Brian Martindale, Bob Ferrett

Congratulations to all! Awards will be presented at State FFA convention in March.

In 2020, the FFA chapters will compete in corn or soybean plots. For more information, visit theagroexpo.com.

post_text: If you have a student interested in Skilled Trades encourage them to participate in our Just Build It Construction Expo field trip on Tuesday, Oct. 22. We go to Eastern Michigan University Convocation Center for hands on activities with skilled trade apprenticeship programs; demonstrations by industry professionals such as architects and engineers; and exhibits by construction firms, educational institutions and industry organizations.This is an excellent opportunity if interested in Skilled Trades! Contact Mrs. Huff ASAP to have your student sign up!

post_text: Tomorrow all of our Juniors will be going to visit Baker College, Jackson College and Spring Arbor University. Lunch will be provided so please attend. All Career Center Student will stay at Springport and go on the College Visits with the rest of the Juniors. post_text: Juniors will be going on a trip to visit 3 local colleges (Baker, Jackson & Spring Arbor) on Oct. 1st. Lunch will be provided for this excellent opportunity to explore how the 3 local colleges can help you meet your college and career goals after graduation.
